comm_lines.comm: Nikita Miller to Shenwari, no run, driven back at the bowler
Nikita Miller to Shenwari, no run, forward and blocked
Nikita Miller to Shenwari, no run, drifting in towards the pads, Shenwari flicks and picks out square leg
Nikita Miller to Shenwari, no run, 86ks on off-stump, punched back to the bowler
Nikita Miller to Shenwari, no run, just a gentle push down the pitch
Nikita Miller to Rahmat, 1 run, sliding in towards off-stump, punched down to long-on
Brathwaite to Rahmat, 1 run, good length ball outside off, angled away past the diving backward point fielder
Brathwaite to Shenwari, 1 run, short and at the body, Shenwari swivels and pulls it backward of square leg, Hetmyer keeps it to one
Brathwaite to Rahmat, 1 run, dug in and Shah pulls it to deep square leg
Brathwaite to Rahmat, no run, fuller and outside off, Shah drives it straight back and big Ricky gets a hand on it in his followthrough
Brathwaite to Rahmat, no run, angled in and Shah drives with a closed bat face to mid-on
Brathwaite to Rahmat, no run, back of a length just outside off, Shah blunts it to backward point
Nikita Miller to Shenwari, no run, closer to the stumps and Shenwari blocks it back
Nikita Miller to Rahmat, 1 run, tossed up and Shah eases the drive to long-off
Nikita Miller to Shenwari, 1 run, fraction short and outside off, punched to sweeper cover

Nikita Miller to Shenwari, no run, dropped! That had to be taken. Gayle the culprit. Not short enough to play the cut and Shenwari still went for it, thick outside edge and it deflected of Hope to Gayle at slip. The big guy could not react quickly to catch that. Went in and out
Nikita Miller to Shenwari, no run, dead-batted back down the wicket

Nikita Miller to Shenwari, FOUR, the runs are starting to flow for Afghanistan. Shenwari fetches the flighted delivery from outside off and sweeps it backward of square leg, no one in the deep there to stop that

Brathwaite to Rahmat, FOUR, third boundary of the over and it is an expensive one from Brathwaite. Short and hurrying the batsman on the hook shot, the top-edge flies away fine beating the fielder in the deep
Brathwaite to Rahmat, no run, back of a length close to off, Shah defends it with a straight bat
Slip has been whisked away

Brathwaite to Rahmat, FOUR, glorious! Right of the cricketing manual. Overpitched by Brathwaite and he's made to pay, Shah leans forward and creams the cover drive through cover. No need to run for those
Brathwaite to Rahmat, no run, on a length and outside off, Shah pushes it to point with a nice stride forward

Brathwaite to Rahmat, no run, similar kind of delivery to the previous one, but the line was wider and Shah is sucked into playing at that, beaten on the outside edge. Just a hint of nibble for Brathwaite

Brathwaite to Rahmat, FOUR, lovely piece of timing. Nothing but a forward push and the ball raced away. Fuller and just outside off, Shah eases it straight of mid-off and Holder does not even bother to chase that
Nikita Miller to Rahmat, 1 run, hammered to long-off
Nikita Miller to Shenwari, 1 run, goes with the arm, takes a thick inside edge through backward square
Nikita Miller to Shenwari, no run, defended from the crease
Nikita Miller to Rahmat, 1 run, punched down to long-off
Nikita Miller to Rahmat, no run, dances down and drives it back
Nikita Miller to Rahmat, no run, quicker on the stumps, stonewalled
Brathwaite to Shenwari, no run, back of a length angled in, tapped to mid-on
Brathwaite to Shenwari, no run, short of length outside off, chopped in front of backward point
Brathwaite to Rahmat, 1 run, short and outside off, Shah upper cuts it to third man
Brathwaite to Rahmat, no run, back of a length around off, blocked
Brathwaite to Rahmat, no run
Brathwaite to Rahmat, no run
Carlos Brathwaite, right-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Nikita Miller to Rahmat, 1 run, an extension of the forward push and the ball rolls away to long-off
Nikita Miller to Shenwari, 1 run, fraction short and Shenwari punches it to sweeper cover
Nikita Miller to Shenwari, no run, nudged gently in front of mid-wicket, sent back on the single
Nikita Miller to Shenwari, no run, nice and slow from Miller, Shenwari drops it dead near his feet
Nikita Miller to Rahmat, 1 run, comes down the track and eases the flighted delivery to long-off
Nikita Miller to Shenwari, 1 run, drifting in with the arm, tucked in front of square on the leg-side
Nikita Miller, left-arm orthodox, comes into the attack
Keemo Paul to Shenwari, 1 run, push and run and Holder at mid-off was more than happy to concede the single, just sits back and allows the ball to come to him
Keemo Paul to Shenwari, no run, back of a length and Shenwari is on the walk as he taps it to cover
Keemo Paul to Shenwari, 2 runs, fullish and outside off, Shenwari eases into the drive and places it wide (left) of mid-off, two more
Keemo Paul to Shenwari, no run, back of a length on off, stonewalled
Keemo Paul to Rahmat, 1 run, shortens the length and is pulled away to fine leg
Keemo Paul to Rahmat, no run, fuller and outside off, Shah push-drives it to mid-off
Holder to Shenwari, no run, wide outside off and Holder gets away with it, Shenwari moved across and let it go, looked at the umpire for an extra and gets nothing in return
Holder to Shenwari, no run, oh! This short of length delivery keeps coming into the Shenwari, who was trying to evade it, the ball thuds into the glove and drops well short of Gayle at first slip
Holder to Shenwari, 2 runs, this time connects with the short of length delivery, gets on top of it and plays a controlled pull past the square leg umpire, two added
Holder to Shenwari, no run, fuller and around off, defended back
Holder to Shenwari, no run, shortens the length and Shenwari is on the hop to tuck it round the corner, misses and is struck on the tummy
Holder to Shenwari, no run, back of a length close to off, Shenwari greets it with a straight bat
Keemo Paul to Rahmat, no run, short of length outside off, ignored
Keemo Paul to Rahmat, no run, back of a length around off, Shah blocks off the back foot
Keemo Paul to Rahmat, 2 runs, full and angled in, flicked elegantly through mid-wicket for a couple
Keemo Paul to Shenwari, 1 run, short and at the body, Shenwari swivels and gloves the pull to fine leg
Keemo Paul to Shenwari, no run, hint of inward movement and Shenwari does not account for it, the drive through the off-side takes the inside edge and rolls to mid-wicket
Keemo Paul to Shenwari, no run, on a length and outside off, Shenwari lifts his bat and lets it go
Holder to Shenwari, 1 run, drifting down leg and Shenwari glances it to fine leg

Holder to Shenwari, FOUR, good fast hands from Shenwari. On a length and outside off, no real foot movement from Shenwari as he drives on the up and places it square on the off-side, the timing takes care of the rest
Holder to Shenwari, no run, missed out there. Short and wide outside off, Shenwari cuts and misses. He went a bit too hard
Holder to Shenwari, no run, back of a length around off, Shenwari bunts it into the off-side
Holder to Rahmat, 1 run, very full and outside off, Shah drives it straight to cover and a casual Samuels lets it through, cost him only a single
Holder to Shenwari, 1 run, Shenwari jumps and tucks the short of length delivery to the vacant mid-wicket region
Keemo Paul to Rahmat, no run, maiden! Excellent over from the young man. Finishes with a back of a length delivery around off, Shah knocks it to cover
Keemo Paul to Rahmat, no run, and again.. After the first couple of deliveries he's looked fairly compact
Keemo Paul to Rahmat, no run, once more right behind the line is Shah to keep it out
Keemo Paul to Rahmat, no run, back of a length on off, Shah is back and across to block
Sivaram says: Just when I was about to say the Afghans need to play safe and win this game, they lose a wicket

Keemo Paul to Rahmat, no run, loud shout for caught behind. Hope and Paul went up in unison. Umpire Gough stays unmoved. That looked close and there was a sound as ball past bat. Back of a length in the channel of uncertainty, Shah looks to defend off the back foot and is beaten. Not sure what the noise was
Keemo Paul to Rahmat, no run, nagging line from Paul. In the corridor just outside off, Shah is lured into the forward defensive and the ball then nibbles away to beat the outside edge
Holder to Shenwari, no run, curling away from short of length, Shenwari lets it pass

Holder to Rahmat, 3 runs, much better from Shah. Rides the bounce on the short of length delivery and punches it square on the off-side, Hetmyer got a hand on that and it took the pace off the ball, three taken
Holder to Rahmat, no run, on a length and outside off, Shah drives on the up and finds the mid-off fielder in the way
Holder to Rahmat, no run, tentative poke. Similar delivery to the previous one, but Shah reckons he needs to have a feel for the ball, leaves his bat hanging away from the body and is beaten
Holder to Rahmat, no run, short of length outside off, Shah watches it sail past him
Samiullah Shenwari, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Holder to Mohammad Shahzad, out Caught by Rovman Powell!! Horrible! Reckless and put any other adjective to that shot. Yes, he plays like that, but when your team needs you, there should be more responsibility. Advances down and Holder smartly keeps it outside off, Shahzad had to reach out and in the end could only manage a cue-end to mid-off. A skier for Powell which he takes without any fuss. Afghanistan in trouble. Mohammad Shahzad c Rovman Powell b Holder 8(12) [4s-1]
Holder to Mohammad Shahzad, THAT'S OUT!! Caught!!
Keemo Paul to Mohammad Shahzad, 1 run, fuller and on the stumps, Shahzad drives it past his partner, Bishoo tumbles across from mid-on to keep it to a single
Keemo Paul to Mohammad Shahzad, no run, short of length around off, Shahzad hops and fends it back to Paul

Keemo Paul to Mohammad Shahzad, 2 runs, hint of width and Shahzad feeds on it, slices the loft over extra cover and has to settle with a brace as the ball plugs in the outfield, Holder doing the tidying up job

Keemo Paul to Mohammad Shahzad, no run, half hearted appeal for caught behind, umpire Michael Gough is not interested. Banged in and Shahzad takes it on, the ball keeps climbing and goes over the top-edge. Not close to the bat
Keemo Paul to Mohammad Shahzad, no run, shortens the length but the line keeps Shahzad calm, defended to mid-on
Keemo Paul to Mohammad Shahzad, no run, fuller and on off, Shahzad defends with the bat and pad close together

Holder to Rahmat, 2 runs, edged and a good stop at third man. The second slip was moved wider after the second delivery. If Nurse had stayed put, he would have had a chance to take that. On a driveable length and Shah is sucked into playing at it, bat well away from the body and the outside edge bisects Nurse and Gayle, Brathwaite puts in a full length dive to save two. He seems to have hurt himself and has gone off the field
Holder to Rahmat, no run, in and around off, Shah is back and across to stonewall that
Holder to Rahmat, no run, on a length and bit of wobble in, Shah covers it with a stride forward
Holder to Rahmat, no run, good length ball outside off, Shah presses forward and defends to point
Holder to Rahmat, no run, back of a length close to off, Shah is compact in his back foot block
Holder to Rahmat, wide, Windies need to be more disciplined. Already the fifth wide of the innings. Holder splays it down leg and Shah had no chance of making contact, too far down
Holder to Rahmat, no run, short of length just outside off, Shah rides the bounce and pats it to cover
Keemo Paul to Rahmat, 1 run, bit of space outside off and Shah uses that to steer a single to third man
Keemo Paul to Rahmat, no run, drags back the length and Shah is comfortable with that, blocked
Keemo Paul to Rahmat, no run, this is a better line and length. On a length and outside off, Shah is drawn into the forward push and the ball nibbles away slightly to beat the outside edge
Keemo Paul to Rahmat, wide, sprays it down leg, Shah gets inside the line and misses the glance, wide called
Keemo Paul to Rahmat, no run, closer to off-stump from short of length, Shah is right behind the line to defend
Keemo Paul to Rahmat, no run, back of a length and curling away outside off, Shah lifts his bat and lets it go
Rahmat Shah, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Keemo Paul to Javed Ahmadi, out Lbw!! First legal ball and Paul strikes. That looked plumb. Not sure why Shahzad was shaking his head at the other end. Good length ball nips back in, Ahmadi is on the move and is beaten on the inside edge, rapped right in front of off-stump. Umpire Gough thought for a split second and raised his finger. Just the start Windies would have wanted while defending this low score. Javed Ahmadi lbw b Keemo Paul 1(2)
Keemo Paul to Javed Ahmadi, THAT'S OUT!! Lbw!!
Keemo Paul to Javed Ahmadi, wide, the debutant starts with a wide outside off, pitches well away and shapes away further
Keemo Paul, right-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Holder to Mohammad Shahzad, no run, rising from a length, Shahzad hops across and blocks
Holder to Mohammad Shahzad, no run, fuller just outside off, Shahzad waits in his crease and tilts his bat to defend it into the off-side
Holder to Mohammad Shahzad, wide, more swing for Holder. Drifting down leg, has to reload
Holder to Mohammad Shahzad, wide, sliding down the leg-side, called a wide
Holder to Mohammad Shahzad, FOUR, typical Shahzad slog. Sees a length around off, gets under it and smacks it straight down the ground
Holder to Javed Ahmadi, 1 run, full and shaping away outside off, Ahmadi gets a soft outside edge. Rolls away to third man
Holder to Mohammad Shahzad, 1 run, first runs for Afghanistan and Shahzad. Shortish from Holder, Shahzad rolls his wrists and controls the pull behind square
Holder to Mohammad Shahzad, no run, on a length and swinging away outside off. Shahzad raises his bat and leaves
Mohammad Shahzad and Javed Ahmadi are at the crease. Mohammad Shahzad is on strike. Holder will open the attack
Welcome back for the chase.

12:56 Local Time, 10:56 GMT, 16:26 IST: Excellent effort from Afghanistan in the field, after Windies elected to bat. They look all business out there, getting into a huddle before striding off. There's still some work to be done, but the bowlers have done their best to set things up. Right from the time Mujeeb knocked over Gayle at the top, the Afghan spinners maintained a stranglehold on proceedings, barely allowing the batsmen any leeway. The pressure was sustained later by Mohammad Nabi, who struck first ball to become the first Afghanistan player with 100 ODi wickets. Rashid was brilliant too. All that pressure paid off with Windies unraveling towards the end, losing four wickets for 11 runs at one stage. It's not over though. We've seen Afghanistan falter in a very similar run-chase before. They can't afford for that to happen today. High pressure chase coming up..

Dawlat Zadran to Nurse, 1 run, premeditates a scoop, Zadran bangs it short outside off and it deflects off Nurse's arm as he tries to get behind the line of it. Rolls towards the keeper. May have been off the glove
Dawlat Zadran to Keemo Paul, 1 run, short of length delivery, 129kph, Paul mistimes his pull in the air. It drops short of deep square leg
Dawlat Zadran to Nurse, leg byes, 1 run, tailing in to hit Nurse's pad, deflects behind point
Dawlat Zadran to Keemo Paul, byes, 1 run, short ball outside off, Paul swings hard on the pull but misses. They steal a bye as the keeper misses his throw
Change of bat for Paul

Dawlat Zadran to Keemo Paul, SIX, picks the slower ball and whacks it away into the grass banks behind deep mid-wicket. It was the back-of-the-hand variety from Zadran, which drifted conveniently into Paul's pads
Dawlat Zadran to Nurse, 1 run, the free-hit is carved straight into the hands of sweeper cover
Dawlat Zadran to Keemo Paul, no ball, 1 run, high full toss from Zadran, Paul swipes hard and mistimes it to long-on. Clearly over the waistline this ball, called a no-ball
Dawlat Zadran [7.0-1-33-0] is back into the attack
Nabi to Keemo Paul, 1 run, fired into the blockhole, Paul rushes his bat down and jams it down to long-off
Nabi to Keemo Paul, no run, looks for a big slog-sweep but misses and is hit on the pad
Nabi to Keemo Paul, no run, drilled straight back to the bowler

Nabi to Nurse, leg byes, 1 run, did he offer a shot there? The umpire hasn't called it a dead ball, so he thinks that he did. Flat on leg, Nurse almost bailed on trying to defend the ball and it deflected off his pad behind square
Nabi to Keemo Paul, 1 run, flat on leg, glanced wide of short fine leg
Nabi to Keemo Paul, no run, darted in at 107kph, Paul fails to dab it away

Rashid Khan to Nurse, no run, oh geez, he has him in such a web. Googly turning in from a length, Nurse initially gets forward to defend, and then tries raising his arms to leave it alone. By the time he does, the ball had already deflected off his gloves into the on-side
Rashid Khan to Nurse, no run, lovely leg-break from Rashid, making Nurse stretch forward in defence and still leaving enough room for the ball to rip past the outside edge
Rashid Khan to Nurse, no run, plays it off the back foot this time and blocks it back down
Rashid Khan to Nurse, no run, he thought it was the googly, closed the bat-face on it. But the ball spun away from him, comfortably beating his outside edge
Rashid Khan to Keemo Paul, 1 run, nicely tucked off the back foot through square leg
Rashid Khan to Nurse, 1 run, went hard at this full ball, may have been the googly and so Nurse skews it off the inside-half towards long-on
Rashid Khan [9.0-1-29-1] is back into the attack
Nabi to Keemo Paul, 2 runs, goes back deep and works it in between long-on and deep mid-wicket, Nurse pushes his partner across for the second
Nabi to Nurse, 1 run, sliding on towards leg and middle from round the wicket, defends softly in front of square leg
Nabi to Keemo Paul, 1 run, Windies nudging and nurdling at the death. Another single into the on-side
Nabi to Nurse, 1 run, nudged into the on-side
Nabi to Keemo Paul, 1 run, flat delivery on leg, tucked through mid-wicket
Nabi to Keemo Paul, no run, glanced to short fine leg
Mohammad Nabi [8.0-1-35-2] is back into the attack
Sharafuddin Ashraf to Nurse, no run, defended off the back foot
Sharafuddin Ashraf to Keemo Paul, 1 run, pushed through the covers

Sharafuddin Ashraf to Keemo Paul, no run, this time. Surely. Not out again. Keemo Paul eating into all of his debutant's luck here. Any one of these two decision could have gone with Sharafuddin, but they're both turned down. Flat on middle and leg, straightens and pins Paul on the back foot. Afghanistan are not amused
Sharafuddin Ashraf to Keemo Paul, no run, plays all across a delivery which drifts in and hits the pad in front of off. Woah, given not out. Was it turning too much to miss off. Not sure about that
Sharafuddin Ashraf to Nurse, 1 run, defended off a thick inside-edge through backward square

Sharafuddin Ashraf to Nurse, 2 runs, slices his cut in the air, but Najibullah can't cling on at backward point. It was a good effort from him, diving across to his right but could only get fingertips
Rashid Khan to Keemo Paul, no run, fired full and wide, squeezed to backward point
Keemo Paul, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Rashid Khan to Rovman Powell, out Caught by Mujeeb!! Windies totally unraveling here. They've now lost four wickets for 11 runs, with the in-form Powell being the latest to go. He looked all at sea against Rashid, decided that sweeping was the way to go, but on the basis of that shot, it clearly wasn't. Thick top-edge on the shot, comfortable catch at deep backward square. Rovman Powell c Mujeeb b Rashid Khan 3(12)
Rashid Khan to Rovman Powell, THAT'S OUT!! Caught!!

Rashid Khan to Rovman Powell, no run, now he exposes his stumps by getting too far across on the sweep, Rashid spots the opportunity and slips in the googly which almost gets through. Powell just about gets a thick under-edge
Rashid Khan to Rovman Powell, no run, plays it late and dabs it with the turn to short third man
Rashid Khan to Rovman Powell, no run, now the leg-break, and he hasn't picked this either. Looks to work it through the on-side and squirts it off the leading edge towards backward point
Fahood says: Shai Hope has a strike rate of 66 in ODI is this a good strike rate at current level ? -- Nowhere close.
Rashid Khan to Rovman Powell, no run, loud appeal as he strikes Powell's front pad with the googly, didn't pick it at all. But the impact is just outside off, so a good call by the umpire
Rashid Khan [8.0-0-29-0] is back into the attack
Sharafuddin Ashraf to Nurse, 2 runs, chipped nicely over extra-cover, with Nurse getting his front leg out of the way and lifting it with the turn
Sharafuddin Ashraf to Rovman Powell, 1 run, tossed up around off, Powell knocks it down to long-on
Sharafuddin Ashraf to Rovman Powell, no run, defended to short cover
Ashley Nurse, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Sharafuddin Ashraf to Brathwaite, out Caught by Rahmat!! Looks to sweep again, but he gets it off a thick top-edge this time. Another one goes. Afghanistan reaping the rewards of maintaining sustained pressure through the middle. Brathwaite has barely had time to get himself in, feels compelled to go for it, and lobs a simple catch to Rahmat at deep backward square. Brathwaite c Rahmat b Sharafuddin Ashraf 4(5) [4s-1]
Sharafuddin Ashraf to Brathwaite, THAT'S OUT!! Caught!!
Sharafuddin Ashraf to Brathwaite, FOUR, plants his front foot across, gets down low and sweeps this off the stumps past short fine leg. Quite well timed from Brathwaite
Durga Sarangi says: Shai Hope.. Good player but playing in Wrong Format
Sharafuddin Ashraf to Rovman Powell, 1 run, flicked away through mid-wicket
Sharafuddin Ashraf [7.0-1-19-0] is back into the attack
Mujeeb to Brathwaite, no run, the carrom ball, kicks up slightly and hits Brathwaite on the bat-shoulder in defence
Mujeeb to Brathwaite, no run, turning in at the stumps, defended to leg
Mujeeb to Brathwaite, no run, handles it well on the back foot
Carlos Brathwaite, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Mujeeb to Shai Hope, out Caught by Najibullah!! Hope's struggles come to an end. Quite a painful innings from him, badly lacking in fluency. He was getting stuck, had to try and break the shackles, and in doing so he perishes. Tried whacking this over mid-wicket, but seemed to have sliced it off the bottom of his bat, hence hitting it a lot straighter than intended. Najibullah runs across for another catch. Shai Hope c Najibullah b Mujeeb 43(94)
Mujeeb to Shai Hope, THAT'S OUT!! Caught!!
Mujeeb to Rovman Powell, 1 run, flat carrom ball at 93kph, Powell works it nicely off the back foot to long-on
Mujeeb to Shai Hope, 1 run, drags the sweep away to deep square leg
Rashid Khan to Shai Hope, 1 run, full leg-break from Rashid, Hope squeezes it down to long-off for one
Rashid Khan to Shai Hope, no run, picks the googly and smothers it back
Rashid Khan to Shai Hope, no run, now he misses an overpitched delivery outside off, really struggling here
Rashid Khan to Shai Hope, no run, too full to sweep. He had to fetch it from outside off as well. Misses out
Rashid Khan to Shai Hope, no run, drifts this in on off, forward and defended
Rashid Khan to Shai Hope, no run, 94kph, turning away sharply outside off. Hope was left wafting at it with no success
Mujeeb to Rovman Powell, no run, pushes the carrom ball through on a length, gets it to grip the surface and gets Powell squared up. Beats the outside edge
Mujeeb to Rovman Powell, no run, tossed up nicely, Powell gets a good stride forward in defence
Mujeeb to Rovman Powell, no run, gets caught in the crease to a length ball which snakes in and almost sneaks through the gate. It would have done so if not for the inside edge
Rovman Powell, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Mujeeb to Holder, out Caught by Najibullah!! Fired in full, prevents Holder from getting under it and brings about the miscue off the toe-end. This is a big wicket for Afghanistan - getting rid of Holder - who was clearly the more dangerous of the two batsmen in the middle. It was hit pretty hard and flat, but it's a regulation catch for long-on. Holder c Najibullah b Mujeeb 28(26) [4s-2 6s-1]
Mujeeb to Holder, THAT'S OUT!! Caught!!
Mujeeb to Shai Hope, 1 run, swept away to deep mid-wicket
Mujeeb to Holder, 1 run, tries for a flat-batted smite, only manages to slice it down towards long-off
Rashid Khan to Shai Hope, no run, played back down the pitch
Rashid Khan to Shai Hope, no run, gets forward this time - the smart thing to do - and defends
Rashid Khan to Shai Hope, no run, what a ripper! Unplayable from Rashid as he turns this away from Hope at 95kph, squared him up completely on the back foot. Even Shahzad couldn't gather cleanly
Rashid Khan to Holder, 1 run, driven to long-off

Rashid Khan to Holder, no run, quicker through the air, 92kph, this time it's the leg-break which turns well past the outside edge as Holder tries to swing down the ground. Didn't pick it by the looks of it
Rashid Khan to Holder, no run, 85kph, probably a googly on off, Holder turns it to short mid-wicket
Rashid Khan [6.0-0-27-0] is back into the attack
Mujeeb to Shai Hope, no run, punched to short cover
Sanjay says: Jason Holder is the best all rounder among what we have seen from West Indies. -- He's improved a lot.
Mujeeb to Holder, 1 run, tossed up outside off, 88kph, Holder leans across and pushes through the covers
Mujeeb to Holder, no run, glanced to short fine leg
Mujeeb to Holder, no run, holds up on Holder as he tries clipping it away, lucky that it fell short of short mid-wicket

Mujeeb to Holder, 1 run, drifting in at the stumps, wristed down to long-on

Dawlat Zadran to Holder, 1 run, half-volley at the stumps, punched to long-on

Dawlat Zadran to Shai Hope, no run, back of a length delivery outside off, dabbed to backward point
Dawlat Zadran to Shai Hope, 2 runs, short and wide, Hope gets on his toes and slaps it wide of sweeper cover

bala says: What according to you is a par score in this ground for this pitch? -- Anything above 250.

Nabi to Holder, SIX, gets down on one knee and bam! He's absolutely nailed this slog-sweep over mid-wicket. They may have lost the ball, prompting the fourth umpire to come out with a replacement. Or did they find it?
Nabi to Shai Hope, 1 run, darted in on a length outside off, steered through the covers
Nabi to Holder, 2 wides, missed stumping! Nabi outfoxed an advancing Holder by firing this down the leg-side, but his keeper wasn't up to it
Nabi to Holder, no run, pushed through on a length, Holder works it to short mid-wicket
Nabi to Shai Hope, 1 run, turning in on middle, clipped through mid-wicket
Nabi to Shai Hope, no run, loopy ball which almost lands in the blockhole on leg, glanced to short fine leg

Dawlat Zadran to Holder, no ball, 1 run, pretty high full toss, Holder defends off a thick inside-edge through square leg. Given as a no-ball, but the ball wasn't over Holder's waist. Should have been the end of the over. Instead, Zadran will have to protect for the free-hit now
Dawlat Zadran to Shai Hope, 1 run, slightly fuller than a good length, creamed through the covers

Dawlat Zadran to Holder, 1 run, back of a length delivery close to off, dabbed behind backward point

Dawlat Zadran to Shai Hope, 1 run, back of a length delivery just outside off, steered down to third man

Dawlat Zadran to Lewis, FOUR, edged and past first slip. Would have been a straightforward catch had there been a second slip. Dawlat Zadran angles it in before getting the away seam movement, catches the outside edge on the poke and the edge flies past the first slip
Mujeeb to Gayle, no run, tosses it up on a length around middle, smothered into the leg-side
Mujeeb to Lewis, 1 run, eased down to long-off

Mujeeb to Lewis, no run, he continues to dart those variations, hits the pad and appeals, very adjacent that and looks out to the naked eye. The umpire says no, and I guess the only thing that could have possibly saved Lewis was the impact which might have been a touch outside off
Mujeeb to Lewis, no run, carrom ball on off, pushed back to the bowler

Mujeeb to Lewis, 2 runs, slides in with the arm, since the length was short Lewis was able to pick the gap through covers with a backfoot punch. There was a direct hit at the bowling end, but Gayle's safe
Mujeeb to Lewis, wide, drifts this down leg, Lewis misses the sweep
Mujeeb to Lewis, no run, dishes it flat just outside off, Lewis prods and blocks
Mujeeb Ur Rahman, right-arm off break, comes into the attack
Mujeeb with a slip in place...
Dawlat Zadran to Gayle, no run, lovely channels from Dawlat Zadran, no room on offer for the big man, Gayle blocks from the crease
Dawlat Zadran to Lewis, 1 run, keeps it tight around off-stump, Lewis hops and pats it past cover-point
Dawlat Zadran to Lewis, no run, walks across and punches this back of a length delivery to mid-on
Dawlat Zadran to Gayle, 1 run, looks to flick round the corner, but the away swing smacks the leading edge and flows down to square third man
Dawlat Zadran to Gayle, no run, darts it back in off the seam, Gayle sits back and taps with soft hands into the off-side
Dawlat Zadran to Gayle, no run, good length, draws him slightly forward and swings it past the outside edge. Terrific start
Gayle and Lewis are at the crease. Gayle is on strike. Dawlat Zadran will open the attack
Time for the anthems. Massive, massive game for Afghanistan. Right then, all set. Gayle to take strike. Dawlat Zadran with two slips in place...
"Pitch is baked hard and dry, groundsman has managed to get a beautiful sheen on it. May turn later on in the day," says Mark Butcher in the pitch report.

Rashid: We didn't play well in the first round, lucky to be here. Want to play good cricket in this round. Learned from the first round. We forgot what happened in the last week. Fresh tournament for us, have to win all the matches. Two changes from the last game.

Holder: We're going to bat first, looks a pretty good wicket. Want to put some runs on the board. Want to tick all of our boxes. Yet to play the perfect game, hopefully this will be it. We could still get more consistency from the top-order. Forced changed: Roach is out, Keemo Paul makes his debut. Nikita Miller comes in as well.

So the news is that Keemo Paul will be making his debut here today. If the name sounds familiar, it's because it was in the thick of the Mankad controversy during the 2016 U-19 World Cup. Afghanistan, meanwhile, are welcoming back Mohammad Shahzad.
Teams:

Afghanistan (Playing XI): Mohammad Shahzad(w), Javed Ahmadi, Rahmat Shah, Najibullah Zadran, Samiullah Shenwari, Mohammad Nabi, Sharafuddin Ashraf, Rashid Khan(c), Gulbadin Naib, Dawlat Zadran, Mujeeb Ur Rahman
Windies (Playing XI): Chris Gayle, Evin Lewis, Shimron Hetmyer, Marlon Samuels, Shai Hope(w), Jason Holder(c), Rovman Powell, Carlos Brathwaite, Ashley Nurse, Keemo Paul, Nikita Miller
Windies have won the toss and have opted to bat

8.45am local: Welcome all to the Super Six stage of the World Cup Qualifiers. Afghanistan are plain lucky to even be here, having been handed a massive lifeline by Nepal. But even still, the road looks very uphill for them as the points are carried through from the Group stages. On the other hand, Windies swept past everyone they faced in Group B. Afghanistan may have beaten them in the past, but this is a pretty powerful Windies unit with the return of Gayle at the top - thereby forming a devastating alliance with Lewis as the Dutch found out. The odds are very much against the Afghans. Can they rise above it? Can they finish in the top two? Toss in a bit..
Teams:

Windies (From): Chris Gayle, Evin Lewis, Shimron Hetmyer, Marlon Samuels, Shai Hope(w), Jason Holder(c), Rovman Powell, Carlos Brathwaite, Ashley Nurse, Kemar Roach, Kesrick Williams, Jason Mohammed, Devendra Bishoo, Nikita Miller, Keemo Paul

Afghanistan (From): Mohammad Shahzad(w), Javed Ahmadi, Ihsanullah Janat, Samiullah Shenwari, Mohammad Nabi, Najibullah Zadran, Sharafuddin Ashraf, Rashid Khan(c), Dawlat Zadran, Mujeeb Ur Rahman, Shapoor Zadran, Rahmat Shah, Afsar Zazai, Gulbadin Naib, Nasir Jamal, Asghar Stanikzai

latest_video.comm: Nikita Miller to Shenwari, FOUR, the runs are starting to flow for Afghanistan. Shenwari fetches the flighted delivery from outside off and sweeps it backward of square leg, no one in the deep there to stop that
